dct_title_s: Map showing the Soo Line, comprising the Sault Ste. Marie & Atlantic and Minneapolis & Pacific railways
dct_description_sm: Cartographic Details: Scale not given.   Covers Michigan, Wisconsin, Minnesota, Iowa and portions of Ontario, Dakota, Nebraska, Illinois, Indiana, and Ohio.   Relief at Turtle Mountains shown with hachures.   Map removed from: Minneapolis: metropolis of the Northwest ; first in grain shipments, foremost in lumber production and the leading flour market of the world. Minneapolis : Star Publishing, 1887.
